before_start: {"blocks":[{"key":"eg5v7","text":"This version is for two virus plates, which corresponds to max. 47 different viruses, and 5 time points (including time point 0). It is assumed that the virion concentration of the virus samples is known (see dx.doi.org/10.17504/protocols.io.6qpvr6q93vmk/v1).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":209,"length":48}],"data":{}},{"key":"9ajh6","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"4hd2i","text":"Use sterile techniques throughout this protocol. Using materials that don't bind viruses is important; see Materials for more information.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":107,"length":10}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"7bhep","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"41kcu","text":"Definitions:","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"2i2co","text":"BBM = modified Bold's Basal Medium, see the associated publication","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"34etu","text":"persistence conditions = the conditions under which persistence is being tested (e.g. a specific temperature)","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"ekc3j","text":"growth conditions = the conditions that allow algae to grow (e.g. 20°C, constant light, on an orbital shaker)","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"5j3na","text":"culture plates = 96-well flat-bottomed tissue culture plates (see Materials)","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":66,"length":9}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"fjl20","text":"deep well plates = 96-well 2.2ml PP deep well plates (see Materials)","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":58,"length":9}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"a4dnh","text":"transparent seal = transparent PCR plate seal (see Materials)","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":51,"length":9}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"link","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"guid":"C7E078C2E69D11ECA1840A58A9FEAC02","url":"http://dx.doi.org/10.17504/protocols.io.6qpvr6q93vmk/v1"}}}}

description: {"blocks":[{"key":"1loi7","text":"This protocol describes a modified persistence assay, as presented in the manuscript \"Life history diversity and signals of trade-offs in a large group of chloroviruses\" (Lievens et al., bioRxiv). It is designed to quantify the specific infectivity and mortality rate of chloroviruses (large, lytic dsDNA viruses). The protocol should also be applicable to other lytic viruses that are large enough to be counted by flow cytometry. For viruses that are not large enough to be counted by flow cytometry, this protocol could be adjusted to start with different MOIs. It would then measure the mortality rate only.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":86,"length":82}],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":187,"length":7}],"data":{}},{"key":"3sp6i","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8gkoh","text":"Compared to a classic persistence assay (or survival assay, inactivation assay, ...), this protocol uses predetermined virion concentrations and non-linear statistical modeling to increase efficiency. Briefly, solutions containing 50000, 5000, 500, or 50 virions*/ml are prepared for each virus, these solutions are split into aliquots, and independent aliquots are used to do an MPN-like assay after 0, 7, 14, ... days. The MPN-like assay involves distributing the aliquots across 16 replicate liquid cultures of host cells (algae) and observing the number of cultures that are lysed. Statistical models are then used to estimate the initial concentration and decline of infectious virions. See the associated manuscript for a full description and schematic figure, as well as the statistical model.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"link","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"guid":"09E92BFF47E711EDB54B0A58A9FEAC02","url":"https://doi.org/10.1101/2022.03.13.484168"}}}}
materials_text: {"blocks":[{"key":"4tjqm","text":"For this protocol, we use:","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"118fj","text":"to store virus samples: 15ml PP centrifuge tubes from Sarstedt (ref. 62.554.502, Sarstedt, DE) - don't interfere with viruses*","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":94,"length":32}],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"9mdd","text":"culture plates: 96-well polystyrene tissue culture plates from Techno Plastic Products (ref. TPP92696, Techno Plastic Products, CH) - don't interfere with viruses*, can withstand centrifugation, and let light through in the persistence conditions","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":132,"length":114}],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"d1i4j","text":"deep well plates: 96-well 2.2ml PP deep well plates from VWR (ref. 732-0585, VWR International, USA) or Abgene (ref. AB0932, Thermo Scientific, DE) - don't interfere with viruses*","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":148,"length":31}],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"64ruh","text":"transparent seals: PCR plate seals from VWR (ref. 732-3212, VWR International, USA) - very adhesive and let light through in the persistence conditions","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":84,"length":67}],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"evs88","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"chbl0","text":"*We find that in many storage containers, the virion concentration decreases over time (EJPL, unpublished data). This includes many types of PCR plates, eppis, and centrifuge tubes. The effect may be because virions adsorb to certain plastics. Any new storage container should be tested before use!","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":0,"length":298}],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":208,"length":34}],"data":[]},{"key":"sj8","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"75kn7","text":"Also necessary:","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"d51dv","text":"up to 47 virus samples","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"3t85","text":"an algal culture in a growth phase that can be infected by the viruses","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"fa9bf","text":"centrifuge with a rotor for plates","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"4qier","text":"vortex","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"1o5nl","text":"multichannel pipettes","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"77h88","text":"haemocytometer and microscope, or some other way of counting algae","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"fb2bf","text":"Parafilm","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"link","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"guid":"8F8EC625E69C11ECA1840A58A9FEAC02","url":"https://www.nature.com/articles/s41598-021-86571-x"}}}}

status.info: We use this protocol and it's working

steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"c87c2","text":"Mix the deep well plates by using a 1000μl multichannel pipette to pipette each column up and down 3x.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"a542c","text":"Using a multichannel pipette, aliquot 200μl from deep well plate \"1\" into five culture plates. These are the virus plates \"1\". Do the same for deep well plate \"2\" and the virus plates \"2\".","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"1hjlk","text":"Seal all but one of the virus plates \"1\" and all but one of the virus plates \"2\" with a transparent seal, and store under the persistence conditions.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"UNDERLINE","offset":5,"length":11},{"style":"UNDERLINE","offset":45,"length":11}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"ac7l5","text":"Count the concentration of algal cells in the algal culture using a haemocytometer.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"bt9k7","text":"Notes: If necessary, centrifuge the algae for 5min at 4500rpm, gently pour off the supernatant, resuspend the pellet, and count the concentration of algal cells in the pellet.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"6kmsg","text":"Using the algal culture and BBM, prepare 590ml of an intermediate algal solution at 1.05*106 cells/ml.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sup","offset":91,"length":1}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"644if","text":"Background info: This concentration is late exponential phase for our algae; the idea is that the algae are concentrated enough for the viruses to lyse quickly, but aren't yet in stationary phase.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"4q6gi","text":"Aliquot 190μl algae into each well of 32 culture plates. These are the MPN plates.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"aoeu8","text":"Using a multichannel pipette (ideally a 12-channel multichannel), distribute 10μl from the each row of the remaining virus plate \"1\" into two MPN plates as shown. Do the same for the remaining virus plate \"2\". It is possible to use the same tips for all the aliquots of a given row. Label each MPN plate with the virus plate number (\"pl1\" or \"pl2\"), virus plate row, and suffix 1 or 2.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"UNDERLINE","offset":107,"length":9},{"style":"UNDERLINE","offset":183,"length":9}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"2cj12","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"304mo","text":"  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"c333n","text":"Background info: This step makes it clear why the initial concentrations maximize the power of the MPN-like assay:","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"560ci","text":"50000 virions/ml concentration = 500 virions in 10μl -\u003e if the initial proportion of infectious virions (the specific infectivity) is 0.001, half of the 16 replicate wells will be virus-positive at time point 0","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"6mjue","text":"5000 virions/ml concentration = 50 virions in 10μl -\u003e if the initial proportion of infectious virions (the specific infectivity) is 0.01, half of the 16 replicate wells will be virus-positive at time point 0","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"b19gs","text":"500 virions/ml concentration = 5 virions in 10μl -\u003e if the initial proportion of infectious virions (the specific infectivity) is 0.1, half of the 16 replicate wells will be virus-positive at time point 0","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"cm0nc","text":"50 virions/ml concentration = 0.5 virions in 10μl -\u003e if the initial proportion of infectious virions (the specific infectivity) is 1, half of the 16 replicate wells will be virus-positive at time point 0","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"image","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"guid":"435E6440E6A311ECBB1F1D543438ACB1","height":336,"id":301872,"is_video":false,"legend":"","mime":"image/png","original_name":"image.png","placeholder":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/jg3ubixmp.jpg","source":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/jg3sbixmp.jpg","type":1,"webp_placeholder":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/jg3tbixmp.webp","webp_source":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/jg3rbixmp.webp","width":550}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"871hn","text":"Close the MPN plates with their lids, wrap the edges in Parafilm to reduce evaporation, and store them under the growth conditions.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"f3eln","text":"After 4 days, check the algal growth in the MPN plates. This can be done by eye, by measuring optical density at 680nm, etc.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"8dmkq","text":"Collect one virus plate \"1\" and one virus plate \"2\" from the persistence conditions. Vortex the plates and spin down.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"7dsds","text":"Use these virus plates to repeat steps 3-5.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}
